Russia and Georgia yesterday deployed troops to stop the ethnic fighting in a seven  kilometer-wide security zone separating rebel South Ossetia from the rest of Georgia.
South Ossetia wants unification with North Ossetia that has been a part of Russia since  Stalin's days This was the first peacekeeping attempt anywhere in the former Soviet  Union, whose disintegration touched off waves of new ethic conflicts between the  Afghan and Romanian borders.
The mission of the peacekeepers is to form a physical  barrier between the two sides.
They wore United Nations-style blue helmets. 
